  "local_port": 56160,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you check an AT&T balance?",
  "response": "To check your AT&T balance, you can use one of the following methods:\n\n### Online\n1. **Visit the AT&T Website:**\n   - Go to `www.att.com`.\n   - Sign in to your AT&T account using your user ID and password.\n   - Once logged in, you can view your current balance under the \"Billing\" or \"My Account\" section.\n\n### Mobile App\n1. **Use the myAT&T App:**\n   - Download the myAT&T app from the Apple App Store or Google Play Store if you haven't already.\n   - Open the app and sign in with your AT&T user ID and password.\n   - Navigate to the \"Billing\" section to view your current balance.\n\n### Phone\n1. **Call AT&T Customer Service:**\n   - Dial 611 from your AT&T mobile phone or call 1-800-331-0500 from any phone.\n   - Follow the automated prompts or speak with a customer service representative to inquire about your balance.\n\n### Text Message\n1. **Send a Text Message:**\n   - From your AT&T mobile phone, text the word \"balance\" to the number 1111.\n   - You will receive a text message with your current balance.\n\n### Automated Phone System\n1. **Use the Automated System:**\n   - Dial `*225#` from your AT&T mobile phone.\n   - You will receive an on-screen message with your current balance.\n\nChoose the method that is most convenient for you, and you'll be able to check your AT&T balance quickly and easily.",
